rasian land mass at their most taut for decades, Putin and Xi publicly took each other's sides in a range of disputes, notably Ukraine, where the West accuses Putin of preparing for war.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1297, \"end\": 1302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4861746419066837e-46, \"text\": \"Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}, {\"begin\": 1375, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999983302946318, \"rank\": 1.6696890068314016e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 1407, \"end\": 1412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4861746419066837e-46, \"text\": \"Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"geopolitical tensions\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1224}, {\"ngram\": \"both sides\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eurasian land mass\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"their most taut\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1283}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"Xi\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"each other's sides\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"a range\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"disputes\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lengthy joint statement released after their meeting occasionally veered into Cold War-era rhetoric, condemning \\\"certain states' attempts to impose their own 'democratic standards' on other countries\\\".\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The lengthy joint statement\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"their meeting\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"Cold War-era rhetoric\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"certain states' attempts\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"their own 'democratic standards\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"other countries\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Such attempts at hegemony pose serious threats to global and regional peace and stability and undermine the stability of the world order,\\\" they said.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such attempts\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1657}, {\"ngram\": \"hegemony\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1669}, {\"ngram\": \"serious threats\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"global and regional peace\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"stability\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"the stability\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"the world order\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1780}]}, {\"sentence\": \"DIPLOMATIC BOYCOTT The United States and other countries have declined to send dignitaries to Beijing, citing alleged human rights abuses, which Beijing denies.\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999930316609562, \"rank\": 6.968387589521796e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\